nodes.prompt:
Produce a COMPLETE snippet file for an ICM 'snippets' layer, ready to save as snippets/<group>/<name>.md. It MUST begin with an HTML-comment metadata block, with VALID JSON inside, exactly in this form:
<!--icm
{ "id": "<kebab-id>", "title": "<short title>", "doc_type": "snippet", "group": "<csharp or powershell>", "summary": "<one sharp line>", "keywords": ["..."], "source": { "origin": "authored" } }
-->
Then a '# Title' heading, a one-line intro, ONE fenced code block with the snippet, and a short '## Notes' only if useful. Keep the code minimal and correct (C# 5 for csharp, Windows PowerShell 5.1 for powershell). Match the style of these existing entries:

--- REFERENCE ---
{context}
--- END ---

Snippet to capture: {request}

Return ONLY the file content (the metadata block followed by the markdown). No commentary, and do NOT wrap the whole thing in an outer code fence.
